<item>
            <title>[FLINK-7774] Deserializers are not cleaned up when closing input streams</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FLINK-7774</link>
                <project id="12315522" key="FLINK">Flink</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;On cleanup of the &lt;tt&gt;AbstractRecordReader&lt;/tt&gt;, &lt;tt&gt;StreamInputProcessor&lt;/tt&gt;, and &lt;tt&gt;StreamTwoInputProcessor&lt;/tt&gt;, the deserializers&apos; current buffers are cleaned up but not their internal &lt;tt&gt;spanningWrapper&lt;/tt&gt; and &lt;tt&gt;nonSpanningWrapper&lt;/tt&gt; via &lt;tt&gt;RecordDeserializer#clear&lt;/tt&gt;. This call should be added.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
