                            <comment id="16194735" author="githubbot" created="Fri, 6 Oct 2017 15:20:40 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;GitHub user NicoK opened a pull request:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/flink/pull/4783&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/flink/pull/4783&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FLINK-7774&quot; title=&quot;Deserializers are not cleaned up when closing input streams&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;FLINK-7774&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;FLINK-7774&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;network&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt; fix not clearing deserializers on closing an input&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ol&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;
	&lt;ol&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;What is the purpose of the change&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ol&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;


&lt;p&gt;    On cleanup of the `AbstractRecordReader`, `StreamInputProcessor`, and `StreamTwoInputProcessor`, the deserializers&apos; current buffers are cleaned up but not their internal `spanningWrapper` and `nonSpanningWrapper` (via `RecordDeserializer#clear()`). This call should be added.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ol&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;
	&lt;ol&gt;
